title: Suresh Rana continues to lead at Raid de Himalaya
text:
SRINAGAR: Nine-time champion Suresh Rana continued to be the leader in the Xtreme category after the third day of the 17th edition of the Raid de Himalaya motorsports rally.
In his Grand Vitara , Rana finished with a fantastic timing of four hours, eight minutes and 40 seconds that have left the spectators in awe at the end of leg 3 as the rally reached here on Wednesday.
He was followed by Raj Singh Rathore (4:11:23 hours) and Harpreet Bawa (4:12:50 hours).
Among the bikers, Arvind K.P., riding his TVS RTR 450, led the pack in a time of three hours, 49 minutes and 25 seconds.
R. Natraj (3:52:04 hours) and Ashish Saurabh Moudhghil (3:58:12 hours) were second and third, respectively.
